parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering box can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels tight or stuck
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel vibrates or shakes
and the vehicle is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The death wobble or shimmy can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or vibrates violently
the steering wheel oscillates or wobbles
and the vehicle is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The front end vibration or shaking can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle vibrates or shakes
the steering wheel feels loose or unstable
and the vehicle is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The front end vibration/shaking can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle shakes violently
the steering wheel vibrates
and the vehicle loses control when hitting bumps or potholes at speeds above 50 mph.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to EGR Cooler and Oil Cooler Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EGR cooler and oil cooler can cause the engine to overheat, leading to a loss of throttle response, white smoke emanating from the exhaust, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine overheats
white smoke comes out of the exhaust
loss of throttle response
the vehicle stalls
and the engine warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EGR valve can cause the engine to run rough, leading to a loss of throttle response, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine runs rough
loss of throttle response
the vehicle stalls
and the engine warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause the engine to overheat, leading to a loss of throttle response, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine overheats
white smoke comes out of the exhaust
loss of throttle response
the vehicle stalls
and the engine warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the FICM can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power brakes and power steering, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls
loss of power brakes and power steering
and the vehicle becomes difficult to steer.
